  "texts": [
    "All ancilla qubits are disentangled from the data qubits and returned to the |0⟩ state.",
    "The previously used ancillae are ready to act as either new data qubits or new ancilla qubits.2.",
    "The amount of spacetime occupied by active ancilla qubits is only O(N), even though the depth is O(log(N)) and there are O(N) ancilla qubits.Thus, once the ancillae are returned to |0⟩, they can begin to assist with the next state preparation, even if the previous state preparation has not been completed.",
    "We can concatenate and stack many of the state preparation circuits one after another.Quantitatively speaking, we can prepare many unentangled copies of the same quantum state|ψ⟩ ⊗w = w-1 s=0 U s |0 n ⟩ ⊗w = 1 ∥x∥ 2 n -1 i=0 x i |i⟩ ⊗w (18)Here U s 's are the same quantum state preparation unitary but acting on different |0 n ⟩ states.",
    "The above equation does not include ancillas that assist the implementation of the U s unitaries: even though the U s 's act on different |0 n ⟩ data registers, they can share many of the same ancilla qubits.We can also prepare many copies of different unentangled quantum statesw-1 d=0 |ψ j ⟩ = w-1 d=0 U d |0 n ⟩ ⊗w = w-1 d=0 1 ∥x d ∥ 2 n -1 i=0 x d i |i⟩(19)Here U d 's are different quantum state preparation unitaries acting on different |0 n ⟩ states and preparing different N -dimensional states described by the vector of coefficients x d. Even though each U d is mathematically different, the exact quantum gate scheduling is the same."
